<font color="#FF0000">AMAZING!</font><br>
<tt>Tue Aug 19 16:35:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was &quot;locked away&quot; for a weekend in a meeting of what we call &quot;The Circle of Friends&quot; to discuss and debate some weighty issues of importance completely unrelated to the issues on these posts. I began to see into what was going on at that meeting in a way I had not seen before. It struck me that the rules of this &quot;Inner Circle&quot; were practiced by many of the individuals present. The experience was amazing.<br><br>
This could be for several reasons.<br><br>
The ways of this Inner Circle are more universal truths than I had prevoiusly thought, or, my 'Nam PTSD way of handling things is lifting a little and I am seeing what has been before me all along, or I was personally behaving in a way where I was treating everyone as honorable, worthy of recognition, and was teaching and learning with patience, and they responded in kind. <br><br>
I kind of like to think it was a combination of all three.<br>
My prevoius participations in these meetings was very much different than what happened over this weekend.<br><br>
I sit here still amazed with it all, like a small child discovering a butterfly for the first time. My White Wolf is here beside me, a very honored companion through the entire time. I feel fulfilled, alive, and energized in a very positive way. I feel a part of a larger whole. I hope it lasts!<br><br>
  
<p><code>-- art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


